# KitchCu Super-Admin Integration Gate (Always)

Before design or code for **any** product feature, run this gate. Fail any row → redesign or wire admin in the **same change**. “Owner PWA only” is not enough when ops/support/monetization touch the feature.

## Mandatory checklist (copy into design pack / PR notes)

| # | Question | If yes → required delivery |
|---|----------|----------------------------|
| 1 | **Kitchen-scoped?** Affects kitchen ops, credentials, modules, marketing, streaming, billing, or customer UX for a kitchen? | **Admin → Kitchens → kitchen workspace** tab/panel + admin API |
| 2 | **Entitlement / monetized?** Unlocked by plan, package, or module? | **Packages** mapper (feature → package → plan) + kitchen **Package** tab; enforce server-side |
| 3 | **Ops / support?** Employees need view, override, or troubleshoot? | Admin API + UI; **RBAC permission** (`resource:action`); `require_admin_permission` |
| 4 | **Cross-tenant risk?** | Tenant filters; no unscoped lists; admin audit on sensitive writes |
| 5 | **Kill-switch?** | Global `feature_flags` and/or kitchen `module_flags`; Control and/or Modules tab |
| 6 | **Credentials?** | Kitchen secrets on kitchen form; **platform** secrets only under **API Keys** |

Deferral allowed only with: tracker note in `docs/ADVANCEMENT-TRACKER.md` + permission code reserved + owner path still tenant-safe.

## Default kitchen workspace tabs

| Tab | Owns |
|-----|------|
| Profile | Status, address, branded summary |
| WhatsApp | Kitchen `phone_number_id` (not Meta app secret) |
| Payments | Kitchen Razorpay / Route (not SaaS Razorpay) |
| Modules | Per-kitchen module flags |
| Package | Assigned package + feature checklist |
| Marketing | Template counts / broadcast module |
| Streaming | Live session summary + streaming/livekit modules |

## RBAC (employees)

- Platform staff live under **Admin → Employees** (CRUD + deactivate).
- Permission codes: `resource:action` (e.g. `kitchens:write`, `packages:write`, `employees:write`, `marketing:read`).
- Role `superadmin` ⇒ `*`. Never ship new `/admin/*` mutations without a permission check once RBAC exists.
- Billing/notification admin routes must validate the same permission model (JWT + DB grants).

## Forbidden

- Owner-only features that support will need with no admin surface
- Plan entitlements only in the frontend
- Platform Meta/Razorpay SaaS secrets on kitchen forms
- Skipping this gate with “UI later” without tracker deferral

## Agent behavior

At the start of a feature task: state which gate rows apply and which admin tabs/APIs you will touch. If none apply, say so explicitly (e.g. pure internal refactor).
